The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | BCCI gags players again
                                                   BCCI gags players again
                      
	Rajkot: After receiving a letter from Cricket Australia (CA) regarding off-spinner Harbhajan Singhs reported comments against some Australian players, the BCCI on Monday warned the Indian players against giving statements in the media.         
	Players should not give media statements. Now that the tour of Australia has ended, they should concentrate on the upcoming South Africa series, BCCI secretary Niranjan Shah said, adding that the Board will take action against those who go against this order.         
	The BCCI has received a letter from CA to stop Indian players from passing remarks in the media against the Australian cricketers, Shah said.           (PTI)                                                                                                                   
